title: [Western Waterway, Charl's Teeth]
description: The gap between the jetty's reach and the Teeth is at its most narrow here, lending more turbulence to this area than others to the north.  Small whirlpools form and dissolve quickly.  Schools of fish dart in and out of them, flashes of silver in the writhing water.
paths: Obvious paths: north, northeast, east, southeast, south, southwest, northwest
